text: Mutia may refer to : * Mutia (gens), a rather obscure plebeian family in Ancient Rome ; Places and jurisdictions * Mutia, Africa, an Ancient city and former bishopric in the Roman Byzacena province, now in Tunisia and a Latin Catholic titular see * Mutia, Zamboanga del Norte,a fifth class municipality in the province of Zamboanga del Norte on Mindanoa island, Philippines
title: Mutia
